# Flow Testnet Configuration Template
# This is NOT a shell script - it's an environment file template
# Copy this file to .env.testnet and fill in your actual values

# Your Flow Testnet account address (starts with 0x, 18 characters total)
FLOW_ACCOUNT_ADDRESS=0xasdadadwad

# Your Flow Testnet account private key (64 character hex string, no 0x prefix)
FLOW_PRIVATE_KEY=123124ascfasderqwa

# Optional: Flow network (defaults to testnet)
FLOW_NETWORK=testnet

# Optional: Flow CLI path (if not in PATH)
# FLOW_CLI_PATH=/usr/local/bin/flow

# Security Notes:
# 1. Never commit .env.testnet to version control
# 2. Keep your private key secure and never share it
# 3. Use testnet tokens only - never use mainnet credentials for testing
# 4. Consider using a dedicated testnet account for development

# How to get testnet credentials:
# 1. Create account: https://flow.com/flow-token/earn
# 2. Get testnet FLOW: https://faucet.flow.com/
# 3. Export private key from your wallet
# 4. Fill in the values above